                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Since people on this board don't seem to enjoy seeing "problem" threads <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> I'd like to start off by saying that I do enjoy playing my enchanter a ton. I'd never switch to another class and currently it does suit my playstyle almost perfectly. 
<br />

<br />
However, I have been in a raiding (time level) guild until recently, where most of the enchanter versatility and flexibility means jack. I have done a ton of Hard ldon adventures and witnessed bard supremacy in CC there,  and heard about the recent nerfs in kodtaz and beyond (I heard everything is now charm immune), and also how some of the kodtaz trials are preferrably done with the use of a bard.
<br />

<br />
CC starts with the pulling. Bards are better at pulling, if only because of fading memory. The ability to wipe aggro is obviously invaluable, and so is the ability to split unlullable mobs with a mez (while running) and then ditching aggro. The bardic advantages at pulling are obvious.
<br />

<br />
Let's look at mezzing. Bard songs do not have a recast time. This means that a bard does not have to wait 2.2 seconds in case of a resist, or to mez another mob after retargetting. Their songs also generate minimal aggro, which is usually a huge advantage, and if they do they can either stand there and take hits a lot more easily than an enchanter due to their vastly superior defensive skills, or they can simply run around since they can cast on the run. Bards also can't be interrupted unless stunned (no channeling checks). Bards can run into problems with 5+ pulls (4+ mobs to mez), but in modern EQ, this just doesn't happen very often. With 3 and less mobs to mez, bards can do it faster, indefinitely (no mana used) and a lot more safely (resists are largely irrelevant to them). 
<br />

<br />
This doesn't mean that bards are superior in <span style="font-weight: bold">groups</span>. The enchanter advantage at damage through charming largely (and maybe entirely) negates the other bardic advantages. 
<br />

<br />
However it does impact the raiding people, or high level players in very high end zones (god trials). Enchanters are by comparison, an obsolete class as charm damage and the ability to maintain a large number of effects in these situations means <span style="font-weight: bold">nothing</span>, since their one marginally useful specialty, crowd control, is done better by another class - that's incidently also much better at doing many other things in that context. 
<br />

<br />
As far as solutions, I am not sure what to do (without nerfing bards). Maybe change the 56+ mez - glamour of kintaz, apathy, sleep, and bliss - to a neg 50 MR modifier to indirectly reduce enchanter aggro and their inability to handle them as well as bards. It's a cheap solution and would trivialize a lot of content, but I haven't been able to come up with outstanding ideas. Or another would be to lower the spell haste lower cap to 2.5 seconds instead of 3.0 seconds so that mez could actually be hasted. That would make up for the recast time, and the absence of channeling requirements for bards. 
<br />

<br />
Any other suggestions?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
