<br />

<br />
The true problem arises in the fact if a chanter gets agro and dies, there goes your cc.  If the shaman dies or whatever, a bard can go ahead and lock down the add and they can say okay wait a second lets get under control and then go.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But the stackable buffs the Bard is playing will drop. Indeed, the presence of Vallon's means that one song a Bard might potentially play (Warsong of Zek) is reduced in value- it still provides a significant damage shield and attack buff. The presence of VoQ means nothing, since you still get full effect from Marr. 
