<br />
That's exactly what he is saying.  The only reason why Enchanters are the ones on raids to do the mezzing is that the bards have something else to do.  The chanter does not do as much and what it does do can be kept up even while mezzing, so it gets left to us.  If a bard can offer buffs that no one else can but at the expense of mezzing of course chanters will be the ones mezzing.  Now you pointed out yourself that they do the CC on raids whenever they have things chanters can't handle (highsun).
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I don't think these perceptions and habits will change- because there are solid game mechanics behind them. When you have the Enchanter running crowd control, the risk is greater to the Enchanter. When you have the Bard running crowd control, the risk is greater to the group/raid. It should be rather obvious which element of risk is more acceptable.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Let's look at this logically for a second.  If the Risk of a bard running crowd control hurts the group ... then what happens whenever the enchanter who just got agro dies and there is no cc left?  I'd like to think a late mez is better than no mez.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
