Bad comparison, and I am sure you know it. Enchanters have 2 problems when it comes to crowd control in raids: 1) it isn't necessary or even useful in the vast majority of the situation  2) they aren't even the best at it.
<br />

<br />
You can't compare *in camp* crowd control to healing in the raiding game. What's more, crowd control is generally done out of camp, and smart guilds use bards to do it.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Enchanters get far more options than Bards do, those options are longer duration, require less of their total effort, are lower resist, and are faster casting. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
