No. Enchanters have less option, the two things going for them is  duration, and slightly less resists, and a bard can go around resists more easily with aggro free MR debuffs. The faster casting isn't true if you consider the absence of spell recovery time for bards.
<br />

<br />
The total resource argument means nothing in a game where pulls aren't large enough anymore to exceed the capacity of a bard, except on a very rare basis, at least as long as we're strictly talking crowd control.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The aggro issue is actually less disadvantageous for Enchanters- who can reduce their aggro- than it is for Bards- who cannot increase it. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
