No, because enchanters as a general rule don't want to generate aggro, because they can't deal with it very well. Bards would like to generate aggro occasionally but have a hard time doing it. You can try twisting it the other way around, but it's an advantage for bards in an enchanter vs bard comparison.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">So the crux of your argument is that Bards are better at crowd control exclusively because their durability outweighs the enormous disadvantages they possess in every other aspect</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
