        <tr>
		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row2"><a name="26962"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Kortar</span></span><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_offline.gif" border="0" align="absbottom" alt="Offline" title="Offline" /><div class="gensmall"><img src="images/ranks/rank_1.gif" alt="Enchanter" title="Enchanter" border="0" /><br />Enchanter</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Joined:&nbsp;19 Jan 2004</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Total posts:&nbsp;15</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Gender:&nbsp;Unknown</div></td>
                <td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a href="viewtopic.php?p=26962&amp;sid=d9798aa9cf04a8c87888835d37842656#26962"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Wed Feb 25, 2004 8:05 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td align="right" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=26962&amp;sid=d9798aa9cf04a8c87888835d37842656"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td></tr></table></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">You can't compare *in camp* crowd control to healing in the raiding game. What's more, crowd control is generally done out of camp, and smart guilds use bards to do it.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
   While healing is inarguably a more universal feature of raids than crowd control, essentially all of your arguments can be used to justify the position "Paladins are better healers than Clerics".  I pointed this out to showcase how weak those arguments were.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">No. Enchanters have less option,</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
   At high levels,
<br />

<br />
   Enchanters: Mesmerize, Charm, Root, Memory Blur, Stun, Pacify
<br />
   Bards: Mesmerize, Highsun, Pacify
<br />

<br />
   And this doesn't count the fact that Enchanters can do things like Pacify from farther out, or gain reasonable aggro so they can kite things without having to be half a zone away from anyone else generating secondary aggro.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">the two things going for them is duration, and slightly less resists, and a bard can go around resists more easily with aggro free MR debuffs.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
   Harmony of Sound takes 3 seconds to cast, and lasts 3 ticks.  As a result, the situation you're trying to argue makes Bards 'better' essentially never occurs.  You simply don't waste 3 seconds with a mob running around in camp to debuff resists first.  You try a mez; and if that doesn't work, you try a mez again.  The chance of both the mezzes failing almost always counterbalances the certainty of not locking the mob down for 6+ seconds while you Harmony of Sound first.
<br />

<br />
   Sure, if Harmony of Sound cast in 1 second, and lasted minutes, Bards would use it all over the place.  But it doesn't.  So Bards can't use it effectively in the manner you describe.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The faster casting isn't true if you consider the absence of spell recovery time for bards.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
   Recovery time occurs after you've cast a spell, so I'm not sure why you're arguing that it's part of 'casting time'.  It obviously isn't.  Now, arguably the 'cyclic rate' of Bard mesmerize is faster, but Enchanters don't have to chain-mez mobs like Bards do.  They just have to mez it once every 45 seconds or so.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The total resource argument means nothing in a game where pulls aren't large enough anymore to exceed the capacity of a bard, except on a very rare basis, at least as long as we're strictly talking crowd control.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
   With 2 or more secondary mobs, an Enchanter can control them without losing any of his effectiveness towards the group.  With 2 or more secondary mobs, a Bard loses essentially all of his direct DPS and the group starts losing the Bard's indirect DPS via their buffs dropping.
<br />

<br />
   Are you claiming the game is so trivialized that we never see 3-mob fights any more?  Because I see them all the time.
<br />
 
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">No, because enchanters as a general rule don't want to generate aggro, because they can't deal with it very well.  Bards would like to generate aggro occasionally but have a hard time doing it.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
   There is no comparison here.  Enchanters get explicit aggro reduction methods.  Bards get zero aggro enhancement methods.  It's like claiming that both Druid nukes and Rogue healing aren't very good.  Well, this is true, but it's a silly comparison.  The marginal value of Druid nukes is vastly greater than the nonexistant value of Rogue healing.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Actually that's not the crux of my argument. I think bards are essentially better at crowd control because of fading memories and their ability to cast on the run. Crowd control is better done out of camp, and bards can deal with it through pulling, or by mezzing adds before they even reach the camp.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
   Many times it's better to do CC out of camp.  But sometimes it isn't, and many times it can't be.  And when those mobs are in camp, who do you get to control them?  An Enchanter.
<br />

<br />
   I could just as easily argue that kiting is a superior form of fighting to tanking.  When you're kiting, you essentially swap out two non-DPS group slots (tank, healer) for two DPS group slots, so you can kill much faster.  But you can't always kite.  The fact that a Druid can run around chain-snaring a non-summoning mob to keep it from hitting anyone doesn't change the fact that a Warrior is a far better tank than a Druid.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
