<br />

<br />
I play EQ with my significant other, who happens to play a 65 bard.  That doesn't stop us from doing anything together.  We do hard LDoN's all of the time, and the groups likes the consistancy we bring.  We are in the same room when we play, not 2 feet from eachother.  The bard pulls, and I do the CC, now there are times when he gets a crit failure on lull, and he may being a few more than planned, but chances are I will know about the # of mobs he is bringing, b/c I am in the room.  
<br />

<br />
Bards aren't bound by mana, thats for sure, but Fading memories takes up a ton of mana (depending on the bards mana pool)  my b/f's bard is lucky to get 4 FM's out before he is oom.  Bard mana regen sucks.  The only thing that hits a bards mana pool is FT.  
<br />

<br />
The whole deal about locking down mobs when they come in is imprtant I agree.  But bards miss notes 'fizzling' for us, more than you would think.  I have had pulls where the bard couldn't get something mezzed right away b/c of a few fizzles and then a few resists, it happens, be we work as a team, and get stuff done.
<br />

<br />
There have been times where it looked like we were going to wipe, and we didn't, and now, our regular hard LDoN group has learned not to ask questions about what we are doing, and just let us do our stuff.  They are believers, they said.
<br />

<br />
True, every class has their pro's and con's, but working as a team, and knowing the other classes flaws, you can achieve more than you could being alone.  I wouldn't take the bard out of my group (nor I would if I could b/c the b/f might be  litttle questionable on that hehe) I am not jealous of what the bard can do, and he's not jeaulous of what I can do..........well wait, yeah, he's jealous b/c he can't charm a pet in hard LDoN and have it out DPS the entire group, and he's jealous that my mana regen is like heaven compared to his, and he's jealous that I don't fizzle as muzh as him, but those are just petty things we tease eachother about.  In the end, the chanter/bard team works out wonderful for us.  
<br />

<br />
I have no idea the point I was really trying to make, besides the fact that our method of stuff works out great for us, and the groups we are a part of.
<br />

<br />
To each is own  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Dellanie Shadowbane
<br />
Coercer of The Commune</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
